deck_excerpt: A Red-Eyes Deck meant for fun! Also no dragoon.
deck_description:
This deck focuses on Archfiend Black Skull Dragon and Red-Eyes Alternative Black Dragon.

----------
Main
----------

Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring and Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit are self-explanatory. Ash can stop your opponent from searching, and Ghost Ogre can destroy their face up card's effect.

Red-eyes Alternative Dragon can be special summoned from your hand by tributing a red-eyes monster from your hand or field. If he gets destroyed by battle or card effect, you could special summon 1 red-eyes monster from your GY to your field, but if it's a red-eyes black dragon normal monster, then it's attack is doubled. So you could play around this if you wanted to.

Red-eyes Black Dragon is fodder for Red-Eyes alternative Black Dragon, or mostly just fusion material for Archfiend Black Skull Dragon and Meteor Black Comet Dragon. Also used for Red-Eyes Flare Metal Dragon.

Summoned Skull is also mainly fusion material for Archfiend Black Skull Dragon and material for Archfiend's Ascent,

Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon is self explanatory. You can special summon any summon-able dragon from your hand or GY once each turn.

Meteor Dragon Red-eyes Impact is used for fusion summon of Meteor Black Comet Dragon or just to re-summon for his effect. He is a Gemini monster though, so just using him for fusion material is viable.

Red-eyes Archfiend of Lightning is the same as meteor dragon red-eyes, mainly for fusion material but if you want, you could summon him. He's also a Gemini.

Red-Eyes Black Flare Dragon is the same as meteor dragon and archfiend of lightning, mainly for use for other cards, not really needed to win. He's also a Gemini.

Red-Eyes Retro Dragon can return your field from destruction if timed correctly, and pretty good overall.

Red-Eyes Fusion is one of the best fusion cards besides the fact you can't summon at all after using it, and you have to use it first before any form of summoning. You can set monsters though.

Red-Eyes Insight lets you search red-eyes fusion easily by sending 1 red-eyes monster from your hand or deck to the GY, which is really more a benefit than a cost.

Monster Reborn is self explanatory.

Infinite Impermanence is a hand-trap, literally, you can activate it from your hand if you do not control no cards during yours or your opponent's turn. It also negates your opponents monster's effects and if it was set before use, you can negate any spell or trap card effects that would be in the same column as this set card.

Evenly matched lets you banish your opponents monster non-targeting, until they have the same number of cards on their field as yours. This can only be activated after the battle phase, both player's. If you control no cards, you could also activate this straight from your hand.

Return of the Red-eyes is like eternal soul but only for normal monsters in your GY when you control a red-eyes monster. So you could special summon 1 normal monster during either players turn once per turn if you control a red-eyes monster.

----------
Extra
----------

Archfiend Skull can prevent your opponent from using card effects when he declares a attack, so your opponent can't use anything when he battles unless they have a card that responds before hand. After he battles, he can shuffle a red-eyes black dragon from your GY into your deck to inflict burn damage equal to the monster's atk.

Meteor Black dragon is a good beatstick and can summon any red-eyes monster when destroyed. He also sends a red-eyes monster from your deck to the GY and deals half their ATK as burn dmg to your opponent.

Red-Eyes Flare Metal Dragon inflicts 500 burn damage each time your opponent uses a card effect. You can also detach one material to special summon a red-eyes normal monster from your GY.

Mecha Phantom Beast Dracossack can detach a material to special summon 2 phantom tokens, then you can tribute any Mecha phantom monsters or tokens to destroy 1 card on the field.

Number 11: Big Eye lets you detach one material to target and take control of one monster your opponent controls, so you could take a boss monster they have that doesn't have target immunity.

Photon Strike Bounzer lets you negate a monster effect on the field then inflict 1000 burn damage.

Archfiend Ascent can deny summoned skull destruction, and if he is destroyed, you can special summon a summoned skull from your hand deck or GY, his name also becomes summoned skull on the field.

Knightmare cards are self explanatory. Phoenix to destroy one spell or trap card your opponent controls, Cerberus to destroy one monster they control in their main monster zone, and unicorn to shuffle one monster they control back into their deck at the cost of discarding 1 card.

Linkuriboh is self-explanatory. You can send black stone of legend to the GY and use it's recycling effect to shuffle a red-eyes from your GY back into your deck and add the stone back to your hand.

----------
Side Deck
----------

Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion is self explanatory. Ghost Belle can stop them from moving cards from the GY.

Framegear Gamma and Frame Driver is self-explanatory, if you had an empty field and your opponent used a monster effect, you could negate and destroy it, special summoning Gamma and Frame Driver to the field, Gamma has to be in your hand, and Frame Driver could be anywhere in the game except from removed from play. They are great at stopping opponent hand traps, so if you find yourself dueling against someone with a million hand traps, they can literally save you.

Nibiru is great if you find yourself against someone with a spam special summoning medical condition, he's able to wipe out their field via tribute, so most cards, almost none, have immunity to Nibiru. They do get a beefy token though, the good news being that the token is a dumb dead card, non-effect, and no protection whatsoever.

Harpie's feather is self-explanatory and raigeki.

Dark ruler no more negates all your opponent's face-up monster effects for the rest of this turn.
Cyber Dragon trap deck at it's core with a couple of more aggressive options

deck_excerpt: Classic D. A. D. You can never go wrong with him.
deck_description:
Discard Peten The Dark Clown from your hand to your GY with Card Destruction, Veil Of Darkness, Hand Destruction, or even used as a cost for Lightning Vortex. Banish him then special summon another Peten from your hand or deck. Tribute summon Curse Of Dragonfire, special summon another Peten, then with COD's effect fusion summon 1 Starving Venom Fusion Dragon from your Extra Deck. Use Foolish Burial, send a monster to the GY then special summon D. A. D. (provided you didn't use Foolish Burial during the previous combo).

D. A. D. can also be summoned by chaining 2 Mystic Tomatoes with 1 Witch Of The Black Forest. Only downside is you must wait a turn before summoning him if you choose to do it this way.

If you're lucky enough to remove from play 3 or more monsters with Pot Of Desires,  you can bring them back to your GY with Burial From A Different Dimension (up to 3 at a time), then freely summon D. A. D.

deck_excerpt:
Get out Blue-Eyes Chaos Max Dragon, Get out Phantasmal Lord Ultimitl Bishbaalkin,
Summon Tokens to your opponents side and Attach with Chaos Max for
deck_description:
So the Goal is to get out Chaos Max, and attack once for Game. Depending on your opening hand, you can get fully set up but most cases you will have to get stuff set up and win the following turn.

Blue-Eyes Abyss Dragon is Key, but to get its effect off you need to make sure you have a Blue-Eyes on the Field or even easier in the GY.

So your objective is to get the Blue-Eyes to the GY, either from Foolish Burial, or dragon shrine. Dragon shrine is clutch because you can get one in the GY, then send an additional dragon since you sent a normal monster first, and you send Stone of Ancients which will help you special summon Abyss at the end phase. So i will usually get out a linkuriboh and chill. Depending on your hand you can go into xyz or even Alt Ultimate Dragon, but most cases you will end with a linkuriboh and possibly a Imperm Set.

Then in the end phase, your Stone of Ancients will activate, special summon the Abyss dragon (I usually do in defense), which in turn will activates abyss effect which you search your Advanced Ritual Art, and the Chaos Max dragon. Now if you have either of those in hand or its more ideal to get a poly then go for it, but in this example you don't have either card.

So next turn you will have an empty board, most likely they killed off your linkuriboh. So you activate Advanced Ritual Art sending the Dragon Core Hexer to the GY, Summoning the Chaos Max Dragon. Now you should have more then enough Monsters in the GY by now, and in the case of this example you have searched or had Chaos Dragon Levianeer in hand already. So what you do is banish 3 light monsters, don't banish the Dragon Core Hexer we need that, summon out your Chaos Dragon Levianeer, activate its effect special summoning the Dragon Core Hexer in defense. Now you can synchro the Chaos Levianeer and the Dragon Core Hexer to make the Phantasmal Lord Ultimitl Bishbaalkin.

Now when that monster gets summoned, you can activates its effect to summon out tokens (o atk, 0 def) to your side of the field, and your opponents side of the field, the amount of tokens depends on how many monster zones are open. Its fills the remaining zones. So now your opponent has atleast 1 token, attack with Chaos Max and game over (8000 Damage).

This isnt some meta beating deck, buts a hell of alot of fun to play. I forget who i saw this strategy from but i changed it up some.

Any way to make it better feel free to comment or message, im no expert and don't know everything so give me some new ideas.

deck_excerpt: Don't let your opponent play the game lol
deck_description: Splashing the musketeer and amazement engines together makes both strategies much more reliable because both contribute to hindering your opponent's ability to break your board. Arlekino provides one extra disruption to the boards regular musketeer decks can provide. He is also a good beat stick and can be used as a material for things like accesscode and apollousa when he is no longer needed. Musketeers in general are a very good control deck because they can search each and every form of negation under the sun, using cards like max and caspar. Your usual win condition is just getting a caspar out and then searching multiple negations off of max, which are later used in caspar's column in order to trigger his effect to search another disruption. After a turn or two your opponent should have burned through their field and hand so they won't be able to do much. Then you will be able to go into either utopia double or accesscode to go for game.

In case anything gets hit with the fairy package, Magikey could be an interesting alternative.

This is a fun Blue-Eyes deck that i made when i saw the potential of Blue-Eyes Abyss Dragon.

It can pop 3 Cards every turn, not just monsters, 3 cards in general. He Also cannot be targeted or destroyed by card effects. So he can still die to battle but he's got 4500 Attack, not the easiest to do in 1 turn.

I put in the Numeron #100 (OTK Package), because its extremely easy to use with Draglubion #97, honestly to good not to use.

I also put in a Nebula to easily get out a Rank 8 xyz.

This isn't a meta deck what so ever but I've had a ton of fun using it.

Worst comes to worst and you go first, you summon out as many big beaters as you can, and you use Skill Drain and play big 3K Beatstick.

deck_description: Here's the best gusto deck I could've made, it's up to day with the recent banlist alongside a few changes since the first version of this deck I posted here. Strategy: The main win condition of the deck is that your opponent should have a high atk monster on their side of the field and be able to summon daigusto sphreez alongside a gusto monster and make your opponent take battle damage attacking with your low atk gusto monsters, although with this deck the main wincon is to summon your big synchro monsters and attack for game. Your windwitch engine will make sure that your plays go through or bait opponent's negations so you can OTK your opponent, not only you can make crystal wing synchro dragon with them but also you can summon Baroness de Fleur in the same turn with your gusto monsters thanks to windwitch glass bell being a level 4 tuner, you can summon her with pilica, descendant of gusto's effect from the gy. The side deck has changed quite a lot ever since a couple of cards got released, like Maple Maiden which is pretty easy to summon and has a deadly combo with Gozen Match , you just declare wind with maple maiden, flip gozen match and now your opponent can only summon 1 monster unless they're playing a wind deck. The same is for secret village of spellcasters, you just summon your windwitch synchro monsters, play secret village and hope that works against the opponent. Other main deck options:   Other side deck options: of course if you have side deck staples like pankratops, red reboot, harpie feather duster, etc. you should definitely use them too! Other cards that you can play in your extra deck: Cards that haven't been released yet that this deck could use: Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon Enjoy!

If you couldn't guess, I really like Gizmeks and Codebreakers lol, even if they aren't super great. This is more of an experiment than a legitimate deck, but it can be fun to test out yourself. Super vulnerable to interruption b/c scrap engine but fairly reliable otherwise. Main combo requires scrap raptor and either recycler or factory. You essentially need to dump four cards to the grave (rosenix, world wand, Taniguku, Uka), so you'll need to summon two golems unless you hard draw foolish burial/succession/reborn. Factory relies on terraforming, but recycler can be searched off of small world if you have one of the gizmeks in hand (banish gizmek from hand, banish scrap raptor from deck, add recycler to hand). There are a few ways to patch up bad hands, you'll most likely just end with less link material on the field in the end. The combo -
  1. Summon raptor, target and destroy itself. Add recycler or factory.
  2. Activate factory
  3. Summon recycler, send rosenix
  4. Banish rosenix for token, link into scrap wyvern
  5. Wyvern summon recycler & destroy recycler
    1. chain link 1 wyvern, chain link 2 factory
    2. factory summon golem A from deck, wyvern summon golem B from deck and destroy factory
  6. Golem A summon recycler, recycler mill world wand
  7. Golem A and recycler link into Lib, Lib adds succession
  8. succession summons golem A
  9. Golem A summon recycler, recycler mill Taniguku
  10. recycler and scrap wyvern link reprodocus
  11. Golem B summons recycler, recycler mill Uka
  12. recycler and Lib link codebreaker virus, virus summon zero day to opponents field
  13. reprodocus make zero day your desired attribute
  14. Link/do other plays (Avramax is a decent option using reprodocus and virus to direct attacks away from the barrier statue)
  15. banish Taniguku from grave to summon Uka, Uka target zero day to summon barrier statue of desired type.
  16. ???
  17. Profit?
If you don't summon Avramax and have a good hand you'll end with two golems and two link 2s on the field before the barrier statue (maybe an Uka if you drew one since it's a free summon during the combo), so you could also make a 4 material Apollousa, or whatever other link plays you want. The provided extra deck only has the bare minimum plus a couple recommended cards. Avramax can draw attacks away from the barrier statue, Apollousa is Apollousa. If you don't want to use zero day or Uka, Reprodocus can make something a winged beast to summon simorgh, who summons the wind barrier in the end phase. If you can't finish the combo, golem can also summon scrap recycler to your opponents field as well, so if you can summon Uka from the hand/graveyard you can put up the earth barrier statue. You can sub in whatever barrier statue you think is most effective, the ones in the main deck are just the most reliable to get out. And if Reprodocus makes zero day the divine attribute, you can summon Obelisk from the deck (Big Meme). This is essentially an engine to search any of Uka's targets while still putting up link material. Nothing competitive, but I like finding weird uses for cards.

deck_excerpt: You know what you're getting yourself into
deck_description:
Instead of dissecting such a skillful and innovative deck down to each individual card, let's just go over the basics.

This is Nurse Burn, and as such, you want to get Nurse on board as soon as you can. To achieve this, we're running four draw cards and six searchers for Nurse. If Nurse or Simochi is not active on your opponent's turn, you lose the game. It's that simple.

The burn cards are as follows: Upstart Goblin, Gift Card, Tri and Guess, Dark Cure, and The Paths of Destiny. The extra deck that I included is specifically for use with Ghost Reaper as this deck dies to a single interaction. If you want Tri and Guess to almost never fail, run an extra deck of fifteen of the cheapest link monsters you have. The Psychic Eraser Laser in the side deck is also a solid burn card, but you need your opponent to play the game first.

Other options for the deck include Mystic Mine as Nurse is unaffected by its restrictions, Soul Taker as a really bad removal option, The Eye of Truth if you want to pretend hand knowledge was worth it in a deck that just spams burn damage, Pot of Extravagance if you can't afford Prosperity, and Forbidden Chalice if you can't afford Forbidden Droplets

deck_name: A little guide to pure stardust
deck_description:
We all know stardust dragon, 5Ds mascot, got its own archetype, and more recently got a set dedicated to it!

I took the new cards for stardust and made a combo deck with it, so here’s the build

1 assault beast for the assault mode engine

1 legatus for my little dragunity engine explained later

3 stardust syncron as your main play starter

3 stardust trail which is part of your main combo

3 ash for negate

3 Remus for dragunity engine explained later

1 baby roc for dragunity engine explained later

3 psi reflector assault mode engine

3 conversing wills dragon for its combos it helps preform

1 brotar, a really powerful extender that’ll be explained later

3 arriving miracle which makes conversing wills worth playing

1 boot sector launch for discard material

3 dragon ravine for dragunity engine explained later

1 absorption for removal

3 stardust illumination as an amazing extender

3 tuning to search stardust synchron

1 assault mode activate for the assault mode engine

3 infinite impertinence for negates and hinderence

2 shooting majestic as a boss monster

1 normal majestic as an alternative boss

1 baroness as a neat gimmick boss

1 crystal wing for deagunity explained later

1 psy framelord omega for hand rip

3 stardust dragon, star of the show

2 stardust spark dragon as an alt star

1 gae dreg dragunity engine explained later

1 charge warrior for a free draw

1 formula synchron free draw

1 striker dragon explained later

So the reason I said explained later so much is because this deck has a 2 card and discard combo with MULTIPLE ways to open. Here’s the multiple combinations

Stardust synchron or tuning plus arriving miracle, stardust illumination, or dragon ravine which requires an additional discard

Stardust trail plus stardust illumination or dragon ravine (requiring another discard) works as well

Synchron and trail also works

Neither way of dragon ravine can be because of remus sadly

Here’s how to start:

If you opened the Synchron path with ravine or illumination use synchron to search arriving miracle, have ravine or illumination dump stardust trail and then link Synchron for striker and search boot sector launch, then tribute boot striker dragon to summon synchron and trail will summon itself too, activate arriving miracle and put conversing wills on top of your deck

If you opened the syncron path with arriving miracle search illumination and then follow the steps above

If you opened the trail path summon trail, link for striker, search boot sector, dump synchron with illumination or ravine, tribute striker to summon synchron, search arriving miracle and summon trail, activate arriving miracle, put conversing wills on top of your deck

If synchron and trail is opened, summon synchron, search arriving miracle, link for striker, search boot sector launch, tribute striker for synchron and trail, arriving miracle place conversing wills on top of your deck

(You must always activate arriving miracle last)

After this proceed with the following steps:

Tune synchron and trail for stardust dragon (summoning a token with trail is not optional, summon it)

arriving miracle draws you a card so draw conversing wills and summon it with its effect, then have it summon brotar from your deck

Brotar target stardust dragon to search remus, discard boot sector launch

Tune your stardust, token, and brotar with conversing wills to summon shooting majestic star dragon

Activate remus from your hand to search dragon ravine

Activate dragon ravine and use its effect to search legatus

Legatus can summon itself from your hand because you own dragon ravine

Because you own a dragunity remus can summon itself from your graveyard

Remus tunes legatus for gae dreg

Gae dreg searches baby roc and discards baby roc

Baby roc summons itself

Tune gae dreg with baby roc for crystal wing

Combo done! You now have shooting majestic star dragon and crystal wing synchro dragon!

Strong points:

Very consistent with multiple ways to summon your boss monsters

Lots of cool combos and really fun to play

Weaknesses:

Pretty underwhelming

Forced to run bricks

Overall I’d say this deck would be good at a locals level depending on your locals, it’s more of a casual deck but it’s fun to play, if I had to rate the archetype out of ten I’d give it a six
